{
  "stem": "10406.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But not much really.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was-- it was a hard-working community.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Even the people that owned stores and owned businesses, and they you could say were 'well off,' quote, they were-- they still worked very hard.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The people in the crafts, they worked all day in their shops.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But life was very happy, especially when the Sabbath came around.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And everything was closed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "All the stores would be closed on the Sabbath.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that possibly was a little bit of a friction type of situation where they probably-- the non-Jews would probably look at this as, look, Saturday I want to go and buy something and all the stores are closed.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But everybody was so religious that they wouldn't dare-- even though they weren't so religious wouldn't dare keep stores open on-- on-- on Saturday.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So Saturday was like a holiday.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And everybody, at least all the men, all the males would go to synagogue.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they would dress up in their Sabbath clothes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And even if they owned one suit, they would put it on on-- on that day and they would look prosperous.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And everybody would come to synagogue clean.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And-- and the synagogue, besides the praying atmosphere, was in a way a social get together type of atmosphere.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had my friends there and we used to get together.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Usually like between prayers when we could get away, we would go behind a certain area and tell stories and go during-- when it was warm go outside and play games and then come back into the synagogue and, you know, continue praying.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The atmosphere in the synagogue was Orthodox, very Orthodox.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Everybody wore long [? talesim. ?] And-- and it was a very sincere type of atmosphere of praying.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
